4 HJR___ COMMENDING SENIOR TROOPER HUNTER WOODRUFF AS A
5 RECIPIENT OF THE 2026 ALABAMA LEGISLATIVE MERITORIOUS
6 SERVICE AWARD FOR LAW ENFORCEMENT.
7
8 WHEREAS, it is with the highest commendation that the
9 Legislature of Alabama recognizes Senior Trooper Hunter
10 Woodruff as a recipient of the 2026 Alabama Legislative
11 Meritorious Service Award for Law Enforcement in recognition
12 of extraordinary courage and decisive action in the line of
13 duty; and
14 WHEREAS, on November 12, 2025, while traveling east
15 on Highway 14 in Autauga County, Trooper Woodruff observed a
16 Prattville Police Department vehicle traveling at a high
17 rate of speed with emergency equipment activated;
18 recognizing the urgency of the situation, he immediately
19 activated his own emergency equipment and followed the
20 officer in order to render assistance if needed; and
21 WHEREAS, Trooper Woodruff followed the Prattville
22 officer to an apartment complex off Covered Bridge Parkway
23 in Prattville, where they were advised of a gunshot victim
24 lying on the ground nearby; upon locating the victim,
25 Trooper Woodruff immediately began rendering lifesaving
26 first aid; and
27 WHEREAS, after identifying two gunshot wounds to the
28 victim's left side, Trooper Woodruff quickly removed the
Page 1

victim's left side, Trooper Woodruff quickly removed the
HJR235 INTRODUCED
29 victim's clothing, applied a sterilized clotting agent, and
30 applied gauze with direct pressure to the wounds, thereby
31 stemming further blood loss; and
32 WHEREAS, Trooper Woodruff continued speaking with the
33 victim to keep him calm and to help prevent the onset of
34 traumatic shock until paramedics arrived on the scene and
35 transported the victim to the hospital for further
36 treatment; and
37 WHEREAS, according to Prattville Fire Chief Josh
38 Bingham, Trooper Woodruff's swift actions and proper
39 application of first aid were instrumental in saving the
40 life of Mr. Gilbert; such conduct reflects the highest
41 standards of the law enforcement profession and exemplifies
42 the courage, dedication, and professionalism expected of
43 those who serve and protect the residents of Alabama; now
44 therefore,
45 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
46 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That we hereby honor and commend
47 Senior Trooper Hunter Woodruff as a recipient of the 2026
48 Alabama Legislative Meritorious Service Award for Law
49 Enforcement and dedicate this resolution to him with
50 profound gratitude, admiration, and esteem for his exemplary
51 service to the people of this state.
